clerics with my wisdom gear on.  Wasn't my idea of how to play a pali.  So how do you all melee and heal with encounters like Tunare, Arche Liche, etc?  <br><br>Irena Viridian<br>Ashen Vendetta<br>Innoruuk Server <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uirenaviridian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irena Viridian</A> at: 2/23/02 10:09:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/22/02 12:25:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> There is really not much we can do in regards to getting so much aggro without us slowing down some. Similar to a wizard we cannot just go all out anymore like in the past without some help.<br><br>If we go full out and cast HWoP every time it becomes available again, then we heal 7,200 HP/min or 120HP/sec. Add a typical 50-70DPS that we paladin do in those fights and you get an aggro rate of 170-190 Damage or Heal per second. That is before we lay hand or cast cel cleansing.<br><br>Against mobs that rate healing similar high as meele damage  there is no chance in the world to avoid aggro. ...<br><br>except when a chanter casting beguiling visage on you. <br><br>So get your local chanters to cast beguiling visage on you shortly after the start of a battle. That will give you a 30% reduction in aggro and should scale you down to 119-133 DH/PS.<br><br><br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uirenaviridian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irena Viridian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/22/02 12:54:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> Thanks Senchy, I'll try it <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upraetorthecrusader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Praetor the Crusader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/22/02 3:17:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.avatarsofdiscord.org/images/membersub/Praetor/myezboardpic5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> Make sure you're standing at maximum melee range as well.  Agro is based a lot on range to your target, especially on undead and certain boss mobs. <p><b><a href="http://209.15.40.226/members/view_member.php?charID=69&userID=20" style="text-decoration: none">Praetor, 60th Crusader</a></b><BR><a href="http://www.avatarsofdiscord.org" style="text-decoration: none">Avatars of Discord</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umurdochmclean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Murdoch McLean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/23/02 11:23:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> I rarely get agro on large scale raids. I keep max distance from the mob, turn off attack when i get agro, Da if i keep agro, and heal from max melee range or a bit further back. It also depends on the mob you are fighting. I for rhaiq1 and 2 in ssra have found they agro you healing alot more so keeping out of the rampage list and in back of it helps alot. If your enchanters are increaseing your MT agro and your MT has good weapons you won't have a problem. I hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufogelxanedu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fogel Xanedu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 637<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 7:26:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/marncrs/pics/fogel2 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> I really only have problems when raids dip below 30 people. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28774>Fogel Xanedu(My Profile)</a><BR><a href=http://www.Thunderwalkers.net>Thunderwalkers</a><BR>Level 60 Paladin<BR>Morell-Thule<BR><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=80 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame/2.png" ALT="What Video Game Character Are You? I am an Asteroid." /></A>I am <B>an Asteroid</B>.<BR /><BR />I am a drifter. I go where life leads, which makes me usually a very calm and content sort of person. That or thoroughly apathetic. Usually I keep on doing whatever I'm doing, and it takes something special to make me change my mind. <A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl">What Video Game Character Are You?</A></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujulesbrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jules Brown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/26/02 9:00:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> Never had this problem.  I'm typically group healing early and often.  I'm meleeing with great weapons.  Even on 2+ pulls I don't really get aggro.  Maybe the warrs I raid with taunt really well...<br><br>Two things that I see newbs doing and dying to unwanted aggro:<br><br>1.  Positioning themselves too close to mob (hoofing the dragon in the nads)<br>2.  Attacking right off the bat.  (I position myself, wait 5 or 10 seconds depending, then attack)<br><br>Cheers,<br>Jules <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujulesbrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jules Brown</A> at: 2/26/02 9:03:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulhile.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lhile</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/6/02 1:46:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fnurt.net/~buckethead/lhilethumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> The only time I've noticed that I take aggro is during the tank switch to our fourth warlord who currently is without her epic weapons or better. I'm right up on the hate list just below the epic'd warlords, so when they die, I'm in trouble. ;-)<br><br>I suppose it's all about moderation... in an encounter where I know I'm going to be healing a lot, I'll often pull out a slightly lower damage weapon such as Jeldorin (19/24 and procs a self heal) so that I can still contribute a reasonable amount of damage, but the combination of that damage and my healing won't get me killed early.<br><br>Ashen Vendetta are a damn fine guild so you've probably got a backpack full of weapons you can play around with. If you find you're getting a lot of healing aggro, try different weapons that might be lower damage or even just without procs (I've seen you carrying an FD around, I think?... That's about the highest aggro weapon we can get. I've found ;-P).<br><br>Amici has finally started on the encounters Ashen have been doing for awhile now (just started killing NToV named, and what not) so I'd love to hear how your experimentation goes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ... Would be nice to know what sort of weapon range we can safely use without drawing aggro through large amounts of healing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Shoot me a tell in game if you give it a try. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Lhile, <p><center><img src="http://www.fnurt.net/~buckethead/lhilesig1.jpg" align=middle></center><br><center><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13716">My Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadronedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MadroneDorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/6/02 11:11:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> Pretty much a rehash of whats already been said but...<br><br>Certain mobs have higher aggro vs healing spells (Direct Healing... Sup/HWoP/LH), I call this &quot;Sont Style Healing aggro&quot; for the mere reason that he was the first guy that i can really remember encountering it on. A few strategies that I use is of course use low aggro weapons (1n nice medium speed, such as massive dragonclaw shard, is great for this,) another to to turn off attack before you cast the spell (sometimes this is undoable as the person or group your trying to health just sorta drops and ya gotta act NOW... turn off attack after the heal... or good old fashion DA. <br><br>Some other mobs that I can think of like this is<br>IV (Akheva Big Boss, The Iktauer Veris or something)<br>Zlandicar (Maybe... only done him once and that was a while ago)<br><br>The Rhags dont seem to be that bad, but the warriors are usally able to hold the rampage, so I dont need to heal much.<br><br>Thought Horror Overlords seems to be pretty cool with healing spells though, used HWoP a few times over the LONG fight after the DoT had eaten away at our healths. (Did the Fizzle curse get removed...? or is there different versions now?)<br>Can anyone else think of Boss's with this &quot;Sont Style Healing Aggro&quot;  attribute? A list of all of them would be nice.<br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50583">Madrone</a> ~ Dorfen Crusader<br>Winter's Light ~ Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uladyslique.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadySlique</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/02 10:45:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro control in high end encounters</span><hr size=1> Dain is also one of the worst mobs for healing aggro. Different mobs react differently to heal aggro for sure.<br><br>I have found the key to the whole thing is simply NOT to be amongst the first three or four healers. If you are going to &quot;heal from the beginning&quot;, then I find you simply have to wait until about 5-7 seconds after the initial engage. <br><br>At that point, the tank has built up some good initial aggro, and the Cheal clerics have also. <br><br>Lhile I haven't seen a FD in Irena's hands for at least ...I don't know...maybe 8 months? Maybe longer.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>We do have a fairly good selection of weapons to choose. Oddly enough I haven't been using any slashing weapons myself for a very long time (except perhaps Dawncaller when doing undead stuff). Mostly switching between the primal lance, rocksmasher and sledge of smashing.  I never thought I would end up using piercing and blunt weapons.  How things have changed.<br><br> <p><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~interruptrequest/slique.jpg"></a> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uladyslique.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadySlique</A> at: 3/17/02 3:32:41 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=14.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=9><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.threadControl?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Old World<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm15">New World<option value="paladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests">Holy Quests<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm12">Equipment Checks<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm13">Crusader's Warhall<op